3.    Purpose of refresh token
        1.Refresh token is a long-lived authorization token  used to generate a new access tokens without asking user to login again.
        2.why refresh tokens needed?
            1.security (limit damage if token is stolen)
            2.stateless scaling
            3.performance

        3.Authentication flow:
            user login
                |
            server verifies credentials
                |
            Generate
                -> Access token(short expiry)
                -> Refresh token(long expiry)

        4.When access token expires:
                client sends the refresh token
                        |
                server validates the token
                        |
                Generates the new token

        5. Token Revocation
            1.Delete refresh token from db
            2.once user logout then token automatically useless


        6.Rotation strategy
            1.old token becomes invalid
            2.new access token issued

        Refresh tokens are used to generate new access tokens instead of asking user to login again due to this improve security and user experience in Authentication systems.

