Difference between Django and FastAPI?

🟢 Django

    A full-stack web framework for Python that comes with everything built-in:

        ORM (database)
        Authentication
        Admin panel
        Templates (for HTML)

    👉 Think: “batteries-included framework”

🔵 FastAPI

        A modern, high-performance API framework focused on building REST APIs using async Python.

        👉 Think: “lightweight + fast API builder”

    Feature	                 Django 🟢	                FastAPI 🔵
    Type	                 Full-stack framework	    API-focused framework
    Speed	                 Moderate	                Very fast (async)
    Async support	         Limited (improving)	    Native async/await
    Built-in features	     Many (ORM, auth, admin)	Minimal (you add what you need)
    Learning curve	         Easier for beginners	    Slightly advanced (async concepts)
    Best for	             Web apps (frontend + backend)	APIs / microservices

 🔹 Real-World Analogy
        Django = 🏠 Fully furnished house
            → Everything ready (kitchen, furniture, electricity)
        FastAPI = 🧱 Custom-built modern apartment
            → You design exactly what you need (but more control)

 🔹 Performance Difference
        FastAPI uses:
            async/await
            ASGI (modern server standard)

        👉 Result: much faster for APIs

 🔹 When to Use Django

    Use Django if you need:

        Full web application (frontend + backend)
        Admin dashboard quickly
        Built-in authentication system
        Rapid development with minimal setup

    👉 Example:

        E-commerce site
        Blog platform
        Internal admin tools

    🔹 When to Use FastAPI

        Use FastAPI if you need:

            High-performance APIs
            Microservices architecture
            Real-time systems
            Async workloads (DB calls, APIs)

        👉 Example:

                Backend for mobile apps
                AI/ML APIs
                High-scale services

    🔹 Important Insight (Interview Gold)

        👉 Django = Monolithic architecture friendly
        👉 FastAPI = Microservices & scalable systems friendly

🔹 Interview Answer (1-minute)

            "Django is a full-stack Python web framework with built-in features like ORM, authentication, and admin panel, making it ideal for rapid development of complete web applications. FastAPI, on the other hand, is a lightweight, high-performance framework designed for building APIs using async programming, making it better suited for microservices and high-concurrency systems."
